# Planner — Improve Pass 2 (delta over planner.out)

Scope of change: ONLY the 3D render + image pipeline. Everything else in
planner.out (Next.js static export, Zustand, PHP-via-Flask backend, cart, audit
section, retro-bowling design, deploy model) stays as-is. Do not rebuild.

## What the user actually wants (from orchestrator2 + 3 screenshots)
- `screenshot owayo.png` = the FIDELITY bar: photorealistic knit jersey, soft
  studio lighting, gradient sublimation, subtle body volume + fabric weave. The
  current flat ExtrudeGeometry (a 0.16-deep silhouette) is explicitly rejected.
- `screenshot bowlifi.png` = the STYLE to match: short-sleeve "Full Custom
  Jersey" bowling shirt, mandarin/placket neckline, button placket, set-in
  sleeves. (owayo 2.png shows the polo/collar family for reference.)
- Core new capability, in priority order:
  1. Upload ANY image → it wraps ALL THE WAY AROUND the shirt (single-image
     wrap mode).
  2. OR upload a separate FRONT image and BACK image (different or same),
     independently aligned.
  3. SMART auto-align: one click re-centers + scales the image onto the shirt
     (deterministic instant; optional WebGPU/WASM vision model refines).
  4. MANUAL adjust: zoom/crop/offsetX/offsetY/rotation sliders that update the
     3D render live (<100ms).
  5. Color pickers + preset patterns still work when no image is uploaded.

## The central technical decision this pass must nail
The whole feature = a **texture-compositing pipeline** feeding a **genuinely
volumetric, well-lit shirt mesh**. Two sub-decisions, both research-gated:

### A. Geometry + material (owayo fidelity)
Replace flat ExtrudeGeometry with a real 3D torso that has proper wrap UVs:
- **Preferred:** a free permissive GLB jersey/polo with clean, known front/back
  UV islands (drei `useGLTF`, static-hostable, <~3MB). Best fidelity, cleanest
  UV mapping for uploads. Gated on RESEARCH Q1.
- **Fallback (if no suitable GLB):** procedural volumetric torso — a lofted body
  from `LatheGeometry`/tapered `CylinderGeometry` (front+back half-shells) with
  proper shoulders, plus set-in sleeve cylinders and a mandarin collar torus.
  Cylinder U maps 0→1 around the body = the wrap requirement falls out for free
  (front at U≈0.25, back at U≈0.75, seams hidden at the sides).
- **Fabric realism regardless of geometry:** `meshPhysicalMaterial` with sheen,
  a seamless knit/fabric **normal map** (subtle weave) + light AO, roughness
  ~0.8, metalness 0; drei `<Environment>` studio HDRI + a soft key/fill
  lightformer rig; `<ContactShadows>` + gentle `<AccumulativeShadows>` for the
  grounded studio look. Gated on RESEARCH Q2 (exact params + a free normal map).

### B. Image pipeline (wrap + front/back + align)
- **One runtime compositor canvas** (e.g. 2048×2048) is the single `map`. Two
  fixed UV rectangles = FRONT island + BACK island of the chosen geometry.
- Each face draws its uploaded image with an affine transform (scale/zoom,
  offsetX, offsetY, rotation), default object-fit COVER. Sliders mutate the
  transform → recomposite → `texture.needsUpdate=true`, throttled to rAF so it
  stays <100ms. Store transforms in Zustand; recomposite in a `useMemo`/effect
  keyed on transform + image (per intake2 useMemo note).
- **Single-image "wrap-all-around" mode:** composite the one image across BOTH
  islands continuously (or `RepeatWrapping` across full U) so the pattern
  circles the whole shirt with the seam at the side. Toggle: `Wrap one image` vs
  `Front + Back separately`.
- **Smart-align (deterministic, instant):** find the image's salient/content
  bounding box (alpha bbox; else variance/edge-energy scan) → compute scale +
  offset to center that box in the island. Must complete <50ms.
- **Smart-align (optional WebGPU/WASM refine, progressive enhancement):** lazy-
  import a client-side vision model to segment the subject / remove background
  and re-center precisely. Deterministic result shows instantly; model refines
  on arrival; never blocks first paint. Gated on RESEARCH Q3.

## Files demo-builder touches (surgical, ~6 files, still under the 12 cap)
- `components/ShirtCanvas.tsx` — swap geometry (GLB or procedural volumetric),
  new fabric material + normal map + studio Environment/lighting, consume the
  compositor texture for front/back islands. Biggest change.
- `components/OptionsPanel.tsx` — add: mode toggle (wrap-one vs front/back),
  Front/Back upload slots, Smart-align button, zoom/crop/offset/rotation sliders;
  keep existing color pickers + pattern presets (shown when no image).
- `lib/store.ts` — add state: `frontImage`, `backImage`, `wrapMode`, per-face
  `{scale,offsetX,offsetY,rotation,crop}` transforms; keep color/pattern state.
- `lib/compositor.ts` (NEW) — canvas compositor: draw image(s) into UV island(s)
  with transform; returns/updates the shared CanvasTexture.
- `lib/smartAlign.ts` (NEW) — deterministic content-bbox align + lazy WebGPU
  refine hook.
- `public/demos/.../assets/` — the GLB (if used) + fabric normal map, hosted
  same-origin.
Keep back-text (Decal) and cart/thumbnail capture working through the new mesh.

## Scope fences (this pass)
1 shirt style (bowlifi short-sleeve custom jersey). Wrap-one + front/back-
separate image modes; PNG/JPG/SVG upload. Smart-align = deterministic always +
WebGPU refine only if Q3 yields a static-hostable model that fits budget (else
ship deterministic-only and describe WebGPU as the enhancement path — do NOT
sink unbounded time). No new backend endpoints required (compositing is client-
side); reuse existing PHP/Flask save-load. Build timeout 3 min.

## Requirement → feature traceability (new rows; prior matrix still holds)
| New requirement | Where satisfied |
|---|---|
| Owayo-level photorealism | GLB-or-volumetric mesh + physical fabric material + normal map + studio Environment/lighting |
| Bowlifi jersey style | short-sleeve custom-jersey silhouette (mandarin/placket) |
| Upload wraps all the way around | wrap-one mode, cylindrical/full-U UVs, side-seam |
| Separate front + back images | Front/Back upload slots → two UV islands, independent transforms |
| Smart auto-align | `smartAlign.ts` deterministic bbox + optional WebGPU refine |
| Zoom/crop/align adjust live | transform sliders → compositor recomposite <100ms |
| Colors/patterns still optional | color pickers + presets active when no image |

## RESEARCH QUESTIONS for pre-researcher (integrate answers, then flip to ready)
1. **Free short-sleeve bowling/polo/custom jersey GLB** with clean, documented
   front-vs-back UV islands: exact URL + license (must be CC0/permissive),
   file size, and how its UVs are laid out (single wrap vs separate panels).
   Candidates to vet: three.js/pmndrs "shirt_baked.glb" T-shirt configurator
   model, Poly Pizza, Sketchfab CC0, Khronos samples. If NONE qualifies, say so
   explicitly so we commit to the procedural volumetric fallback.
2. **Owayo-level fabric realism in r3f within budget:** concrete recipe —
   `meshPhysicalMaterial` params (sheen, sheenRoughness, roughness, clearcoat?),
   which drei `<Environment>` preset (studio/warehouse/city) + lightformer rig,
   AccumulativeShadows vs ContactShadows, and a **free CC0 seamless knit/fabric
   normal map URL** (+ optional roughness/AO map). Give hex-free numeric params.
3. **Client-side smart-align vision model (optional refine):** lightest WebGPU/
   WASM option that runs in-browser, lazy-loaded, static/CDN-hostable — e.g.
   `@huggingface/transformers` RMBG-1.4 background removal, or MediaPipe
   ImageSegmenter, or a saliency model. Give model id, approx size, WebGPU vs
   WASM fallback, and confirm it works from a static site (no server). Plus the
   best **deterministic** content-bbox algorithm (alpha bbox / variance scan)
   with brief pseudocode as the always-on baseline.
4. **Texture-compositing + UV-island technique in three.js:** confirm single
   CanvasTexture (updated on transform, `needsUpdate`, rAF-throttled) is the
   right call vs two textures/materials; how to define/reserve fixed FRONT and
   BACK UV rectangles on the chosen geometry so images stay on the correct face
   with the seam hidden at the sides; and how to keep recomposite <100ms.
5. **Seamless wrap-all-around:** how to map one rectangular image around a
   cylindrical/paneled torso without ugly side-seam distortion (RepeatWrapping
   vs ClampToEdge vs mirrored seam, overlap trick), and any owayo-style
   flat-pattern-to-panel projection worth mimicking.

## handoff
- produced: improve-pass plan delta — replace flat ExtrudeGeometry with a
  volumetric owayo-fidelity shirt (GLB preferred, procedural fallback) + a
  canvas texture-compositing pipeline for wrap-one and front/back-separate image
  upload, smart-align (deterministic + optional WebGPU), live transform sliders;
  colors/patterns retained; ~6 files, backend untouched.
- decisions: single compositor CanvasTexture with FRONT/BACK UV islands;
  cylinder U = natural wrap; fabric realism via meshPhysicalMaterial + normal
  map + studio Environment; deterministic align always-on, WebGPU refine
  optional/gated; no new endpoints.
- next needs: pre-researcher answers Q1–Q5 (esp. Q1 GLB availability decides
  geometry path, Q3 decides WebGPU model). Then planner flips to ready and
  demo-builder edits ShirtCanvas/OptionsPanel/store + adds compositor.ts,
  smartAlign.ts.
- risks: no suitable free GLB → procedural volumetric must still hit owayo bar
  (lighting/material carry it); WebGPU model size/budget; side-seam distortion
  on wrap; recomposite perf <100ms; keep back-text Decal + cart thumbnail
  working through the new mesh.

PLAN-STATUS: needs-research — missing: (Q1) a vetted free permissive short-sleeve jersey GLB with known front/back UVs or confirmation none exists; (Q2) exact r3f fabric-realism params + a free seamless normal map URL; (Q3) a static-hostable client-side WebGPU/WASM align model id+size + deterministic bbox algorithm; (Q4/Q5) confirmed UV-island + seamless-wrap technique.
